Subject: [PATCH 3/3] harden(contacts): single-use QR token + rate-limits +
 body caps
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Single-use import token: payload carries a random nid; the phone route
  claims contact-import:<nid> via claimOnce/email_send_ledger before the
  upsert, so a captured/leaked token works at most once (409 on replay).
  Reuses the proposal-nonce single-use seam; no new table; degrades to
  TTL-only if the ledger migration is absent.
- Per-IP rate limit (inline, house pattern) on /phone, /google/start,
  /upload — these aren't in the middleware RATE_LIMITED_PREFIXES. Added
  rateLimitHeaders() to lib/rate-limit.ts.
- Pre-parse 5MB body cap on /phone + /upload (413) — was only post-parse
  row caps.
- fetchAllConnections bounded at 50k connections (upsert stores <=10k).

tsc 0, eslint clean, next build compiles + typechecks, 3090 tests pass
(+2 token nid tests).

