+## 2026-06-20 (claude/branch-status-check-84t7dh) — harden: single-use QR token + rate-limits + body caps on contact-import
+
+- **Single-use QR token (the deferred residual):** `contact-import-token.ts` now carries a random `nid`; `app/api/email/contacts/phone` claims `contact-import:<nid>` via `claimOnce` (`lib/email/idempotency.ts`) against `email_send_ledger` — atomic `INSERT…ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`, the same single-use seam proposal-nonce uses. A captured/leaked token now works **at most once** → replay returns **409 token_already_used**. Degrades to TTL-only if the ledger migration isn't applied (claimOnce 42P01 → win), never worse than before. **No new table.**
+- **Rate-limits (inline, house pattern):** added `rateLimitHeaders()` to `lib/rate-limit.ts` and guarded the 3 abuse vectors not covered by the middleware prefix list — `/phone`, `/google/start`, `/upload` → **429** with `Retry-After`/`X-RateLimit-*`.
+- **Body-size caps:** `/phone` + `/upload` reject `content-length > 5 MB` **before** `req.json()` → **413** (was: only post-parse row caps; a 50 MB CSV/JSON would parse into memory first).
+- **Bounded Google fetch:** `fetchAllConnections` stops at 50k connections (upsert stores ≤10k anyway) — caps memory on a giant address book.
+- **Note:** single-use also bounds the phone best-effort `syncUserAudiences` amplification the audit flagged (≤1 sync per token), so that broad sync is left as-is.
+- **Gates:** tsc 0, eslint clean, `next build` ✓ Compiled + ✓ TypeScript (env-gated `/charts` only), **3090 tests / 0 fail** (+2 token nid tests). Pushed to `claude/branch-status-check-84t7dh`.
+
